                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d762">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.00/602: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-06T21:00:00+09:00"
                            >March 6, 1936—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 6—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Hirota is now endeavoring to form a Cabinet but has met certain difficulties,
                    apparently with the army, and has not yet succeeded.</p>
                <p>The appointments of Yuasa [as] Lord Keeper of the Seals, and of Matsudaira,
                    formerly Ambassador to Great Britain, as Household Minister have been
                    announced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
